# git-svn-interface
Common interface to use Git/Svn repositories

# API Reference

Inside the exported object, there is an 'svn' and a 'git' object - both have the same functions.
All asynchronous methods return an ES6 promise.

In order to identify the master branch, other branches, and tags, the library uses what it call 'target descriptions' -
these are just objects with the format

```
{ name: 'branchName', type: 'branch' }
{ name: 'tagName', type: 'tag' }
{ name: '', type: 'trunk' } // master branch on git
```

Passing 'null' where the functions expect a target description will default to the trunk/master.

Example
```
var gsi = require( 'git-svn-interface' );
gsi.svn.isWorkingCopyClean( '/home/user/wc' )
	.then( function( isClean ) {
		console.log( "Complete!" );
	} );
gsi.git.cat( 'git@server:/var/repo', null, 'file.txt' )
	.then( function( contents ) {
		console.log( "Complete!" );
	} );
```

